author: Rob Ludacer and Jessica Orwig
title: Watch the government create the world's largest 3D-printed object in under one minute
text:
embed 
This is the world's largest 3D-printed object. It was printed at Oak Ridge National Lab , a nd took 30 hours to make. It's a tool that will help Boeing build aircraft wings . Preliminary tests show it's lighter, cheaper, a nd just as strong as the current tool. 
Video courtesy of US Department of Energy and Boeing.
